    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-05T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="297"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/72: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Addis Ababa</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cramp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-06T01:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 6, 1936—1 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 5—8:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>293. Italian headquarters at palace have sent me captain, lieutenant, and 50 men.
                    Have had them placed outside Legation compound. They inform me nearest occupying
                    force 6¼ miles away. Also that between 25 and 30 thousand Italians here so that
                    by morning the situation will be entirely under control. The city is now calm
                    with only an occasional shot.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cramp</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
